==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Lepidodendron
<hw>Lep`i*do*den"dron</hw> <pr>(-dr⟦ocr⟧n)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[NL., fr. Gr. <grk>lepi`s</grk> <grk>-i`dos</grk>, a scale +
<grk>de`ndron</grk> tree.]</ety> <fld>(Paleon.)</fld> <def>A genus of
fossil trees of the Devonian and Carboniferous ages, having the exterior
marked with scars, mostly in quincunx order, produced by the separation
of the leafstalks.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Lepidoganoid</ent>⟦br⟧
